article.headline: Winthrop 88, UNC Asheville 69
article.story: ASHEVILLE, N.C. (AP) -- Michael Jenkins scored 25 points to lead Winthrop to an 88-69 Big South Conference win Saturday over UNC Asheville. Other Eagles in double figures were Phillips Williams with 19, Taj McCullough at 13 and Antwon Harris, 10. The victory was the 11th straight conference win for Winthrop (19-4, 9-0 Big South), which shot 54 percent from the floor and 89 percent from the free-throw line. The Bulldogs (7-16, 3-6) had 20 points from Bryan Smithson. K.J. Garland also had 14 points, along with eight rebounds.
